cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.RO, cs.DM 

The paper deals with the application of reinforcement learning to improve the performance of integer programming solvers. This involves designing a deep RL formulation, network architecture, and algorithms for intelligent adaptive selection of cutting planes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves optimization and decision-making, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
